                " ATOMIC ENERGY RESEARCH LABORATORY, MUSASHI",
                " INST. OF TECHN., KAWASAKI. K.H., O.A., T.M."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "2JPNJPN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " CENTURY RESEARCH CENTER CORPORATION, TOKYO,",
                " H.K."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " TRIGA-II, 100 KW REACTOR AT MUSASHI."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " THERMAL NEUTRONS FROM THE REACTOR, FILTERED",
                " THROUGH A 30 CM LONG NEARLY PERFECT SINGLE CRYSTAL",
                " SILICON ROD. BEAM BURSTS OF 275 MICROSEC LENGTH (FWHM)",
                " WAS OBTAINED BY A BORON-NITRIDE CHOPPER, 12 CM IN DIA-",
                " METER AND 12 CM HIGH, HAVING NINE SLITS OF 0.4 CM X",
                " 7.0 CM. THE ROTATION FREQUENCY WAS 2000 RPM. THE",
                " NEUTRON BEAM WAS COLLIMATED TO 4 CM DIAMETER. THE",
                " ENERGY RESOLUTION WAS 18 PERCENT AT 0.0253 EV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".SILICON FILTERED THERMAL NEUTRON SPECTRUM."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " TRANSMISSION MEASUREMENT USING TIME-OF-FLIGHT",
                " TECHNIQUES WITH A FLIGHT PATH OF 6.77 M."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " THREE BORON-TRIFLOURIDE COUNTERS WERE SET AT THE",
                " END OF THE FLIGHT PATH."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".SAMPLES OF 99.9 PERCENT PURITY SM2O3, GD2O3 AND DY2O3",
                " WERE USED. THE OXIDE POWDER WAS DILUTED WITH AL METAL",
                " POWDER OF 99.98 PERCENT PURITY. THE SAMPLE HOLDER WAS",
                " A CYLINDER, 64MM IN DIAMETER AND 20 MM THICK, MADE OF",
                " ALUMINUM. THE DENSITY OF THE SAMPLES WAS ADJUSTED TO",
                " GIVE 20 PERCENT TRANSMISSION.",
                ".THE BACKGROUND WAS MEASURED BY COVERING THE SAMPLES",
                " WITH A CADMIUM PLATE OF 1.3 MM THICKNESS."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".THE TRANSMITTED SPECTRA WERE CORRECTED FOR MEASURING",
                " TIME, NUMBER OF CHOPPER ROTATIONS, THE MONITORED",
                " REACTOR POWER AND THE BACKGROUND NEUTRON COUNTS."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " THE TOTAL ERRORS WERE COMPOSED OF THE",
                " FOLLOWING CONTRIBUTIONS. DENSITY OF THE SAMPLE, THICK-",
                " NESS OF THE SAMPLE, STATISTICAL ERROR OF SIGNAL AND",
                " MONITOR NEUTRON COUNTING."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".TOTAL CROSS SECTIONS WERE OBTAINED BY DIVIDING THE",
                " OPEN BEAM SPECTRUM BY THE TRANSMITTED NEUTRON",
                " SPECTRUM."
              ]
            }
          ],
